  "description": "The 0.5 release story: tq2 becomes the default tier (recall-neutral, leaner than int8), the multi-tenant density wedge, tight-container survival and cost, single-tenant scaling tiers, the tiering cold-start bulkhead control-plane feature, and throughput / latency under load. All numbers measured single-machine on Apple Silicon (M1); RAM ratios are hardware-independent, absolute latencies and build times are not. Recall is against exact brute-force cosine ground truth; RAM via ps -o rss.",
